      "date": "2011-07-01 04:47:54.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Verified; Looks good to me, but someone else must approve\n\n(1 inline comment)\n\nClient: 2.0.63\nServer: 1.8.6\n\nStarting client: fat-amd-3-ib: -o user_xattr,acl,flock fat-amd-1-ib@o2ib:/lustre /mnt/lustre\nmount.lustre: mount fat-amd-1-ib@o2ib:/lustre at /mnt/lustre failed: Protocol error\n\n\nDmesg on the client:\n\nLustre: Server MGS version (1.8.6.0) is much older. Consider upgrading this client (2.0.63)\nLustre: 9736:0:(sec.c:1474:sptlrpc_import_sec_adapt()) import lustre-MDT0000-mdc-ffff880103a7dc00->192.168.4.132@o2ib netid 50000: select flavor null\nLustreError: 170-6: Server lustre-MDT0000-mdc-ffff880103a7dc00 does not support feature(s) needed for correct operation of this client (1040001000). Please upgrade server or downgrade client.\nLustre: Server lustre-MDT0000_UUID version (1.8.6.0) is much older. Consider upgrading this client (2.0.63)\n\nIt's better to improve the \"Consider upgrading this client (xxx)\" message also. It should be sth like \"Consider upgrading the server.\"",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
