      },
      "date": "2011-08-12 16:53:12.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4: Verified\n\nFYI, I verified with debug messages (not included in the patch) that I'm accessing the right ocd_connect_flags, and that it correctly detects the missing flags and refuses to connect when trying to mount a 1.8, and in this new version it prints out the missing features by name instead of just the feature numbers:\n\nLustre: Server mds-myth-0_UUID version (1.8.6.80) is much older. Consider upgrading server or downgrading client (2.0.66)\nLustreError: 170-6: Server myth-MDT0000-mdc-ffff8800d8559000 does not support feature(s) needed for correct operation of this client (fid_is_enabled,full20). Please upgrade server or downgrade client.",
